snippet.textDisplay:
I hated this film for one simple reason. The writers clearly just said "well the only good terminator films were the first two so let's just slam them both together into one film".

"In T1 the time travelling hero is a human, in T2 it's a machine, in Dark Fate she's both a human and a machine"

"In T1 the villain is a machine with a solid exoskeleton covered in living tissue, in T2 it's a machine made of liquid metal that can turn it's arms into blades, in Dark Fate it's both."

"In T1 the terminator goes back in time to kill the mother of the saviour of humanity, in T2 the terminator goes back to kill the saviour himself, in Dark Fate the protagonist spends half the film thinking she is the mother and then finding out that she is the saviour. A revelation that served no purpose other than to make this film both T1 and T2."
